    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix operator precedence issue causing buffer overread in EPS QoS decoding\n\n### Summary\nThe EPS Quality of Service IE decoder contained an operator precedence bug in conditional length checks that could lead to buffer overreads when processing optional bit rate fields. The issue occurred when the decoder incorrectly evaluated whether sufficient data was present to decode the extended bit rates structure.\n\nUnder certain network conditions where QoS structures contain partial bit rate information, this bug caused the decoder to attempt reading beyond the end of the provided buffer, leading to potential segfaults in the NAS processing thread.\n\nThe root cause was improper grouping of arithmetic operations with ternary conditional expressions when calculating minimum length thresholds.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EpsQualityOfService.c`: Added parentheses to fix operator precedence in length comparison expressions\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/UeNetworkCapability.c`: Applied same fix to prevent similar issue in UE capability decoder\n\n"
}